[h1]PhobosLib — Changelog[/h1]



[h2]v1.59.0[/h2]
[list]
[*] add Text Compositor utilities (v1.59.0)
[*] add recipe & configuration utilities (v1.58.0)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.57.0 — PhobosLib v1.57.0[/h2]
[list]
[*] add getPlayerPerkLevel safe perk lookup (v1.57.0)
[*] add filterByField utility (v1.56.0)
[*] add infrastructure utilities — manhattanDistance, consumeItems, grantItems, checkRequirements (v1.55.0)
[*] add getRegistryDisplayName utility (v1.54.0)
[*] add formatPlayerLocation() for combined address+room display (v1.53.0)
[*] add PhobosLib_ChunkedWriter for staggered file I/O (v1.52.0)
[*] add lazyInit() and throttle() utilities (v1.51.0)
[*] add PhobosLib.approach() smoothing utility (v1.50.0)
[*] add Schema, Registry, and DataLoader modules (v1.49.0)
[*] add math/table utilities (clamp, lerp, randFloat, round, map, filter)
[*] add sanitiseUsername() to prevent JVM crash on special chars
[*] add strict mode — sandbox-gated pcall bypass for debugging
[*] add PhobosLib_Milestone generic milestone tracker
[*] add findItemsByTag and countItemsByTag utilities
[*] add PhobosLib.notifyOrSay() for unified PN/say fallback
[*] add PhobosLib.generateId() unique ID generator
[*] add automated changelog generation from conventional commits
[*] add getItemDisplayName() and rollChance() utilities
[*] (Fix) resolveAddress returns nil when no street or intersection found
[*] (Fix) add missing _TAG argument to PhobosLib.debug calls in Address and World modules
[*] (Fix) tostring() boot buffer flush to prevent __concat on nil
[*] (Fix) make debug() and trace() nil-safe with tostring()
[*] (Fix) harden hasTag pcall + add split() and hasTrait() utilities
[*] (Fix) guard titleCase gsub callback against Kahlua null captures
[*] add cross-module communication pattern to error-handling guide
[*] add Per-Player ModData Access section
[*] add Empty-Data Return Convention to error-handling guide
[*] add Chunked File Writing section to error-handling.md
[*] add lazyInit and throttle utility documentation
[*] document logging levels and debug vs trace gating
[*] sync deny-list with 2-arg debug/trace detection rule
[*] add PZ API deny-list scanner to catch known-bad Java method calls
[*] extract helpers, consolidate duplicates, bump v1.42.0
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.30.0 — PZ 42.15 OnCreate Compatibility (2026-03-18)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]iterateItems(items, callback)[/b] — Universal items iteration helper that handles both ArrayList (PZ 42.14, size/get) and table/KahluaTable (PZ 42.15) items parameter types from OnCreate callbacks. Prevents hard crashes on PZ 42.15.3.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]averageStampedQuality crash[/b] — Fixed hard crash when items parameter lacks size() method (PZ 42.15.3). Now uses iterateItems().
[*] [b]averageInputQuality spam[/b] — Fixed ExceptionLogger stack traces from pcall-closure pattern. Converted to pre-flight type guards.
[*] [b]degradeFilterFromInputs consistency[/b] — Converted to use iterateItems() for uniform iteration.
[*] [b]Tooltip collectLines() spam[/b] — Added type guard + method-ref pcall for getFullType() to prevent ExceptionLogger stack traces when hovering items.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.29.0 — Quality V2 API (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]calculateOutputQualityV2(input, factor, skillMult, variancePct)[/b] — Fully multiplicative quality formula replacing the additive V1 system.
[*] [b]getSkillMultiplier(player, perk, maxEffect)[/b] — Multiplicative skill bonus (1.0 at Level 0, 1.0+maxEffect at Level 10).
[*] [b]randomBaseQualityV2(min, max, skillMult, variancePct)[/b] — Source recipe quality with multiplicative skill + variance.
[*] [b]getEffectiveYield(value, yieldTable, globalMult)[/b] — Yield tier lookup with sandbox multiplier support.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] V1 functions (calculateOutputQuality, getSkillBonus, randomBaseQualityWithSkill) marked @deprecated but remain functional.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]degradeFilterFromInputs spam[/b] — Replaced pcall-with-closure guard with pre-flight type checks to avoid PZ ExceptionLogger console spam on safe-variant hazard recipe crafts.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.28.0 — World Container Iteration (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Module[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_WorldContainer[/b] (server) — iterateWorldContainers(callback) scans all items in world containers (grid square objects + vehicle parts) across loaded cells. Designed for save migration systems converting items in fridges, crates, shelves, and vehicle storage. All iteration pcall-wrapped.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.27.0 — Recursive Inventory Search & Safety Check (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]findItemByFullTypeRecurse(inventory, fullType)[/b] — Search main inventory + all equipped bags
[*] [b]findItemFromTypeListRecurse(inventory, typeList)[/b] — Recursive type-list search
[*] [b]countItemsFromTypeListRecurse(inventory, typeList)[/b] — Recursive type-list count
[*] [b]findFluidContainerWithMinRecurse(inventory, fluidNames, minAmount)[/b] — Recursive fluid container search
[*] [b]isAreaSafe(player)[/b] — Mirrors vanilla sleep safety check (no visible/chasing/nearby zombies)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.26.0 — Inventory Search by Type List (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]findItemFromTypeList(inventory, typeList)[/b] — Find first item matching any fullType in a list
[*] [b]countItemsFromTypeList(inventory, typeList)[/b] — Count items matching any fullType in a list
[*] [b]findFluidContainerWithMin(inventory, fluidNames, minAmount)[/b] — Find fluid container with minimum fill level
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.25.0 — Player ModData Table Utility (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Function[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]getPlayerModDataTable(player, key)[/b] — Safe getter ensuring a named sub-table exists in player modData. Eliminates repetitive md[key] = md[key] or {} boilerplate.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.24.0 — World Utilities (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]getGridSquareAt(x, y, z)[/b] — Safe wrapper for getCell():getGridSquare() with nil cell handling.
[*] [b]findNearbyVehicles(player, radius)[/b] — Returns all vehicles within radius sorted by distance (unlike findNearbyVehicle which returns only the nearest).
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.23.0 — Vehicle Battery & Template Utilities (2026-03-17)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]getVehicleBatteryCharge(vehicle)[/b] — Safe pcall wrapper returning 0–1 battery charge.
[*] [b]drainVehicleBattery(vehicle, amount)[/b] — Safe VehicleUtils.chargeBattery wrapper.
[*] [b]verifyVehicleTemplatePart(partId, modPrefix)[/b] — Runtime check for template override conflicts with console warning.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.22.0 — Vehicle, Corpse & Experimental Features (2026-03-16)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Vehicle[/b] (shared) — findAllNearbyVehicles() for multi-vehicle scanning.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Corpse[/b] (shared) — getCorpseAge(), getCorpsesOnSquare(), getCorpsesInRadius() for dead body utilities.
[/list]

[h3]New Feature[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]EnableExperimentalFeatures sandbox toggle[/b] — Shared option allowing all Phobos mods to gate WIP content behind one toggle. PhobosLib.isExperimentalEnabled() getter for consumer mods.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] Module count: 24 to [b]26[/b] (15 shared + 11 client/server)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.21.0 — Farming Spray Deprecation (2026-03-16)[/h2]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]registerFarmingSpray() deprecated[/b] — The farming spray registration API still works but is now marked @deprecated with a one-time runtime warning. Mods should output vanilla gardening spray items directly from recipes instead (Base.GardeningSprayMilk, Base.GardeningSprayAphids, Base.GardeningSprayCigarettes, Base.SlugRepellent). The function will be removed in a future release.
[*] [b]Farming spray system rewritten from scratch[/b] — Complete rewrite of PhobosLib_FarmingSpray.lua with clean monkey-patch architecture, pcall-wrapped injection, quantity submenus, drag-to-next-plant cursor, and CFarming_Interact.onContextKey support.
[/list]

[h3]CI[/h3]
[list]
[*] Expanded luacheck globals from PZJavaDocs lua_api.json.
[*] Added copyright headers to JSON translation files.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.20.0 — Multi-Version Support (2026-03-11)[/h2]

[h3]Added[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Multi-version folder structure[/b] — Mod content split into common/ (shared Lua code), 42.14/ (Lua .txt translations for PZ 42.14.x), and 42.15/ (JSON translations for PZ 42.15+). PZ automatically selects the correct version folder.
[*] [b]PZ 42.14 backward compatibility[/b] restored — minimum game version lowered from 42.15.0 back to 42.14.0.
[/list]

[h2]v1.19.0 — PZ 42.15 Translation Migration (2026-03-10)[/h2]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PZ 42.15 translation migration[/b] — Converted all translation files from Lua .txt table format to flat JSON (.json). Files renamed: IG_UI_EN.txt → IG_UI.json, Sandbox_EN.txt → Sandbox.json. 22 keys across 2 files.
[*] [b]Minimum game version[/b] bumped from 42.14.0 to 42.15.0.
[*] CI: sandbox completeness check and encoding validation updated for JSON translation files.
[/list]

[h2]v1.18.2 — Filter Degradation Fix (2026-03-09)[/h2]

[h3]Fixed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Filter degradation crash[/b] — degradeFilterFromInputs tried getDelta/setDelta (DrainableComboItem methods) on gas masks, but B42 masks are Clothing items. Accessing non-existent methods threw in Kahlua, producing stack traces on every safe-variant hazard recipe craft. Switched to condition-based degradation (getCondition/setCondition) with probabilistic loss for low-ConditionMax masks (2–3). ~40 crafts per filter across all mask types.
[*] Removed noisy debug print() from degradeFilterFromInputs.
[/list]

[h2]v1.18.1 — Farming Spray Bug Fix (2026-03-09)[/h2]

[h3]Fixed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]Farming spray context menu[/b] — ISContextMenu in B42 does not have getOptionCount() or getOptionFromIndex() methods. The context menu scanning code silently failed inside pcall blocks. Custom spray options now correctly appear in the "Treat Problem" submenu. Replaced with ipairs(context.options), getOptionFromName(), and getSubMenu(opt.subOption).
[*] [b]Patch retry[/b] — _patchesInstalled flag only set after patches succeed, allowing retry on failure.
[/list]

[h2]v1.18.0 — Debug, Moodle & Fermentation Modules (2026-03-08)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Debug[/b] (shared) — Centralised debug logging system. `PhobosLib.debug(modId, ...)` prints tagged messages when a mod's EnableDebugLogging sandbox option is true.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Moodle[/b] (client) — Moodle Framework soft dependency wrapper. Register custom moodles, set/get moodle levels. No-op when Moodle Framework is not installed.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Fermentation[/b] (shared) — Fermentation registry and progress tracking for items using ReplaceOnRotten as positive curing. Register items, query progress (percent, remaining days), stamp/read game dates.
[/list]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]unconsumeSandboxFlag(modId, varName)[/b] — Re-enable a previously consumed one-shot sandbox flag for re-runnable operations.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] GitHub Actions CI with luacheck validation
[*] Module count: 22 to [b]24[/b] (13 shared + 11 client/server)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.16.0 — Skill Quality Bonus & Popup Enhancements (2026-03-06)[/h2]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]getSkillBonus(player, perk, divisor)[/b] — Convert perk level to a quality bonus
[*] [b]randomBaseQualityWithSkill(min, max, player, perk, divisor)[/b] — Skill-aware source quality generation
[*] [b]averageStampedQuality(items, default)[/b] — Average condition of stamped items only (excludes unstamped/vanilla items)
[*] [b]skillBonus[/b] parameter on calculateOutputQuality() — Additive skill bonus (backward-compatible)
[*] [b]isPlayerAdmin(player)[/b] — Admin check (SP always true, MP checks access level)
[*] [b]registerNoticePopup(modId, noticeId, options)[/b] — Third popup type with shouldShow gate and amber accent
[*] [b]Series-aware popup consolidation[/b] — Tabbed popup grouping across mod families via options.series
[*] [b]i18n popup strings[/b] — All popup fallback text converted to safeGetText() with 11 translation keys
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]setConditionPercent() clamping[/b] — Now clamps to maxCond-1 to prevent setting condition to the "unstamped" sentinel value
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.15.0 — Empty FluidContainer Condition Reset (2026-03-05)[/h2]

[h3]New Function[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]registerEmptyConditionReset(modulePrefix, guardFunc)[/b] — Register a condition reset for empty FluidContainer items. When the player opens or views a container, any empty FluidContainer matching the prefix has its condition restored to ConditionMax. Removes the "(Worn)" suffix from items that repurpose condition as a metadata channel (e.g. purity). Optional guard function controls when resets are active.
[/list]

[h3]Changed[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_VesselReplace[/b] refactored to two-phase system — Condition reset (phase 1) runs before vessel replacement (phase 2) in the same event hook, guaranteeing correct execution order.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.14.0 — World Actions, Entity Rebinding & Fluid Utilities (2026-03-05)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_WorldAction[/b] (client) — Generic world object context menu system. Register custom right-click actions on world objects with requirement checks. Unavailable actions shown in red with reason tooltips.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_EntityRebind[/b] (server) — Server-side entity rebinding for pre-existing world objects. Ensures workstations placed before a mod update get their new entity scripts applied on game load.
[/list]

[h3]New Functions[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]findEmptyFluidContainer()[/b] — Find empty FluidContainer in player inventory matching valid types
[*] [b]tryGetFluidName()[/b] — Safely retrieve fluid type name from a FluidContainer
[*] [b]stampFluidContainerQuality()[/b] — Stamp condition-based purity on filled FluidContainers after +fluid output
[*] [b]recoverDrainedFluidQuality()[/b] — Recover purity from FluidContainers after -fluid drain
[*] [b]getConditionPercent() / setConditionPercent()[/b] — Normalised 0-100% condition helpers regardless of ConditionMax
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] FluidType resolution in tryAddFluid() — resolves string names to FluidType objects for B42 recipe compatibility
[*] Player-vs-inventory parameter handling fixed in find* functions; world action menu deduplication
[*] onContextKey wrapper signature corrected to (player, timePressedContext)
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.13.0 — Popup System & Workstation Labels (2026-02-23)[/h2]

[h3]New Modules[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Popup[/b] (client) — Generic popup system for PZ B42 mods. Two registration functions:
  [b]registerGuidePopup[/b] — First-time welcome guide with "Don't show again" checkbox, per-character persistence, MP sync.
  [b]registerChangelogPopup[/b] — Version-based "What's New" popup that fires once per major.minor version change with content filtering.
  Queue system shows guides first, then changelogs, one at a time.
[*] [b]PhobosLib_WorkstationLabel[/b] (client) — Automatically filters untranslated tags (e.g. CannotBeResearched) from the crafting window's "Requires: ..." workstation label. Supports both vanilla and Neat Crafting UIs. No public API — fully self-contained.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] Workstation label filter now hooks Neat Crafting's NC_RecipeInfoPanel when installed
[*] Changelog popup correctly detects fresh installs (nil stored version = show all)
[*] buildContent callback now receives lastSeenVersion for filtering
[*] Corrected translation table reference from IG_UI to IGUI
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.12.0 — Powered Workstations (2026-02-23)[/h2]

[h3]New Module[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_Power[/b] (client) — Powered CraftBench entity support with 5 public functions:
  [b]isGridPowerActive()[/b] — Check if the electrical grid is still on.
  [b]hasPower(square)[/b] — Check any power source (grid, generator, custom).
  [b]registerPowerSource(checkFunc)[/b] — Register custom power sources (e.g. battery+inverter).
  [b]registerPoweredCraftBench(entity, options)[/b] — Register an entity as requiring electricity. Greys out craft button with tooltip when no power. Options: messageKey, drainPerMinute, guardFunc.
  [b]startPowerDrain / stopPowerDrain[/b] — Time-based generator fuel drain sessions.
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]v1.11.0 — Farming Sprays & Tooltip Guards (2026-02-22)[/h2]

[h3]New Module[/h3]
[list]
[*] [b]PhobosLib_FarmingSpray[/b] (client) — Register custom crop cure sprays that appear in the B42 "Treat Problem" submenu and respond to the Interact hotkey on diseased plants. Hooks ISFarmingMenu and CFarming_Interact, pcall-wrapped. Supports Mildew, Flies, Aphids, and Slugs cure types.
[/list]

[h3]Bug Fixes[/h3]
[list]
[*] Tooltip render replacement now guards against nil self.tooltip during edge-case render calls, preventing crashes when multiple tooltip-modifying mods are active
[/list]

[hr][/hr]

[h2]Summary[/h2]
[list]
[*] [b]26 modules[/b] total (15 shared + 11 client/server)
[*] [b]~150 public functions[/b]
[*] [b]v1.30.0[/b]: iterateItems() for PZ 42.15 OnCreate compatibility, tooltip guard fixes
[*] [b]v1.29.0[/b]: Quality V2 API (multiplicative skill/variance/yield), degradeFilterFromInputs spam fix
[*] [b]v1.28.0[/b]: World container iteration for save migrations
[*] [b]v1.22.0–v1.27.0[/b]: Vehicle, Corpse, WorldContainer modules; recursive inventory search; experimental features toggle; player modData table utility
[*] Requires Project Zomboid Build 42.14.0+
[/list]
